ZCZC GE67
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
WEDNESDAY TO SATURDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND
COASTGUARD AGENCY AT 012300 UTC
ON WEDNESDAY EVENING A CYCLONIC FLOW WILL AFFECT ALL
PARTS WITH LOW PRESSURE 993 EXP TO BE CENTRED OVER
CENTRAL SCOTLAND BY MIDNIGHT THURSDAY. CURRENT
EXPECTATIONS ARE THEN FOR THE LOW TO TRANSFER E ACROSS
THE NERN N SEA DURING THURSDAY AS A FLN FEATURE WITH
PRESSURE RISING TO THE W. ON FRIDAY A CYCLONIC FLOW IS
LIKELY TO PERSIST IN THE FAR E OF THE FCST AREA BUT WITH
A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE BLDN IN THE W. THE PRESSURE THEN
DECLINES FM THE W THROUGH SATURDAY WITH A CYCLONIC FLOW
DEVELOPING IN THE FAR NW BY SATURDAY EVENING. NO GALES
ARE FCST IN THE CULLERCOATS AREA DURING THIS FCST PERIOD
BUT WINDS ARE LIKELY TO BE STRG AT TIMES OVER THE N SEA
PERHAPS MORE ESPECIALLY FOR A TIME IN THE S ON THURSDAY.
THE LOW PRESSURE IN THE FAR NW ON SATURDAY COULD BRING
NEAR GALE FORCE WINDS TO FAIR ISLE BY SATURDAY EVENING
